HEADWORD: Intermarriage
<hw>In`ter*mar"riage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Connection by
marriage; reciprocal marriage; giving and taking in marriage, as between
two families, tribes, races, castes, or nations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

